        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 4:39PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 439 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Adena, or 25 miles south of Fort Morgan, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree branches and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shamrock.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to minor low
land flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
